2014;;The Color of Time;;American;;Various;;James FrancoHenry HopperMila KunisZach Braff;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Color_of_Time;;The different parts of Pulitzer Prize winner C.K. Williams' life told through his poems. Flashbacks of his childhood, his teens, college years, to when he meets and marries his wife, Catherine (Kunis) and the birth of his children and parenthood. The film is narrated by different versions of Williams (Franco, Hopper, March, Unger), depicting the different aspects of Williams through the years.[1]